{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.15",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 15,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 15",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 15 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:1",
      "text": "But Job answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:2",
      "text": "Will a wise man give for answer a mere breath of wisdom? and does he fill up the pain of his belly,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:3",
      "text": "reasoning with improper sayings, and with words wherein is no profit?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:4",
      "text": "Hast not thou moreover cast off fear, and accomplished such words before the Lord?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:5",
      "text": "Thou art guilty by the words of thy mouth, neither hast thou discerned the words of the mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:6",
      "text": "Let thine own mouth, and not me, reprove thee: and thy lips shall testify against thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:7",
      "text": "What! art thou the first man that was born? or wert thou established before the hills?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:8",
      "text": "Or hast thou heard the ordinance of the Lord? or has God used thee as his counsellor? and has wisdom come only to thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:9",
      "text": "For what knowest thou, that we know not? or what understandest thou, which we do not also?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:10",
      "text": "Truly among us are both the old and very aged man, more advanced in days than thy father.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:11",
      "text": "Thou hast been scourged for but few of thy sins: thou hast spoken haughtily and extravagantly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:12",
      "text": "What has thine heart dared? or what have thine eyes aimed at,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:13",
      "text": "that thou hast vented thy rage before the Lord, and delivered such words from thy mouth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:14",
      "text": "For who, being a mortal, is such that he shall be blameless? or, who that is born of a woman, that he should be just?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:15",
      "text": "Forasmuch as he trusts not his saints; and the heaven is not pure before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:16",
      "text": "Alas then, abominable and unclean is man, drinking unrighteousness as a draught.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:17",
      "text": "But I will tell thee, hearken to me; I will tell thee now what I have seen;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:18",
      "text": "things wise men say, and their fathers have not hidden.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:19",
      "text": "To them alone the earth was given, and no stranger came upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:20",
      "text": "All the life of the ungodly is spent in care, and the years granted to the oppressor are numbered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:21",
      "text": "And his terror is in his ears: just when he seems to be at peace, his overthrow will come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:22",
      "text": "Let him not trust that he shall return from darkness, for he has been already made over to the power of the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:23",
      "text": "And he has been appointed to be food for vultures; and he knows within himself that he is doomed to be a carcase: and a dark day shall carry him away as with a whirlwind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:24",
      "text": "Distress also and anguish shall come upon him: he shall fall as a captain in the first rank.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:25",
      "text": "For he has lifted his hands against the Lord, and he has hardened his neck against the Almighty Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:26",
      "text": "And he has run against him with insolence, on the thickness of the back of his shield.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:27",
      "text": "For he has covered his face with his fat, and made layers of fat upon his thighs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:28",
      "text": "And let him lodge in desolate cities, and enter into houses without inhabitant: and what they have prepared, others shall carry away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:29",
      "text": "Neither shall he at all grow rich, nor shall his substance remain: he shall not cast a shadow upon the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:30",
      "text": "Neither shall he in any wise escape the darkness: let the wind blast his blossom, and let his flower fall off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:31",
      "text": "Let him not think that he shall endure; for his end shall be vanity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.32",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:32",
      "text": "His harvest shall perish before the time, and his branch shall not flourish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.33",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:33",
      "text": "And let him be gathered as the unripe grape before the time, and let him fall as the blossom of the olive.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.34",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:34",
      "text": "For death is the witness of an ungodly man, and fire shall burn the houses of them that receive gifts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.15.35",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:35",
      "text": "And he shall conceive sorrows, and his end shall be vanity, and his belly shall bear deceit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
